    "body": "\r\n\r\n\r\n## Purpose\r\nTop issue: for topk=1024 and MTP=1, this kernel will deadline since there's no enough SMs to launch the grid and since each kernel is persistent, no kernel will finish. Hence the process will hang. \r\n\r\nQuery occupancy for the actual <TopK, vec_size> instantiation being launched, reserve one CTA per SM as headroom for co-resident kernels on other streams, and TORCH_CHECK that total_ctas does not exceed the hardware-resident cap. Without this the cooperative spin-wait barrier deadlocks whenever any CTA in a group fails to be scheduled co-resident.\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\n## Test Result\r\n\r\n---\r\n<details>\r\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\r\n\r\n- [x] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\r\n- [x] The test plan, such as providing test command.\r\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\r\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n",
